body:
I am using connectInfiniteHits to show results. 
When a user clicks on an item and then goes back to the search page, I would like him/her to be approximately at the same place on the search page, or at least have the same results presented.

The issue is that when the user comes back to the search page, the pagination seems to have an issue. 
Say I have 7 pages of results in total
If the user was on the 5th page > clicks on a hit > goes back to the page, then the connectInfiniteHits will only show 2 pages of results before the `hasMore` flag becomes `false`.

So my question would be, how to load directly the 5 first pages of results when going back to the result page ?


Here is the website where you can see it happening : [](https://laloc-staging.firebaseapp.com)

Here is the code used using 
react-infinite-scroller v1.1.4
react-instantsearch  v4.5.2 



````
const NeverEndingResults = ({ refine, hits, hasMore, searchKey, page=1 }) => (
    <InfiniteScroll 
      pageStart={page}
      loadMore={refine} 
      hasMore={hasMore} 
    >
      {hits.map(hit => 
        <AlgoliaHitObjects
          hit={hit} 
          key={hit.objectID} 
          searchKey={searchKey} 
        />
      )}
    </InfiniteScroll>
  );

  const createURL = state => `?${qs.stringify(state)}`;

  const searchStateToUrl = (props, searchState) => searchState ? `${props.location.pathname}${createURL(searchState)}` : '';

  const urlToSearchState = (location, initial=false) => qs.parse(location.search.slice(1));
  const updateAfter = 700;

  const MyInfiniteResults = connectInfiniteHits(NeverEndingResults);

  const Search = (props) => (
    <InstantSearch 
      appId="XX"  
      indexName="objects" 
      apiKey="YY" 
      searchState={props.searchState}
      onSearchStateChange={props.onSearchStateChange}
      createURL={createURL}
    >
      <Configure hitsPerPage={12} />
        <SearchBox translations={{placeholder: props.placeholder}}  />
        <MyInfiniteResults searchKey={props.searchKey} page={props.page}  />
    </InstantSearch>
  );

export default class SearchObjectContainer extends Component {
    constructor(props) {
      super(props);
      this.state = {
        searchState: urlToSearchState(this.props.location, true), 
        pageStart: 0, 
        placeholder: "foo
      };
    };

    componentDidMount () {
      if (this.props.location.search.indexOf('page') > -1) {
        const obj = urlToSearchState(this.props.location)
        this.setState({ search: true, pageStart: parseInt(obj.page, 10) });
      }
    };

    componentWillReceiveProps(props) {
      if (props.location !== this.props.location) {
          this.setState({ searchState: urlToSearchState(props.location) });
      }
    };

onSearchStateChange = searchState => {
      clearTimeout(this.debouncedSetState);
      this.debouncedSetState = setTimeout(() => {
        this.props.history.push(
          searchStateToUrl(this.props, searchState),
          searchState
        );
      }, updateAfter);
      this.setState({ searchState });
    };
    render () {
        return (
        <Search 
          searchState={this.state.searchState}
          placeholder={this.state.placeholder} 
          searchKey={this.props.location.search}
          onSearchStateChange={this.onSearchStateChange}
          page={this.state.pageStart}
        />
        )
    }
}

Thanks !

````
